<Author>Mr. MJB
<Content>Acceptable hotel but pricey This is a pleasant hotel, recommended by a Hong Kong resident ex pat. Not the best hotel we have stayed in in Hong Kong and this was our 10th visit. We were upgraded to De-Luxe but frankly could not fathom why it was so called. Had great view of the waterfront and perhaps that is why. The room was light and airy and house keeping was excellent but overall it was a little tired. The room also appeared to have been designed for smaller races than Europeans as the bath was small and we had to duck under the shower but these are small matters. The bed was queen size and comfortable. Position good enough and plenty of eateries nearby and a Delifrance opposite for breakfast ( although the service was appalling and slow with aggressive staff and some clearly did not love their job or their customers!!) For a new visitor to Hong Kong I would recommend a hotel closer to the heart of things back towards Tsim Sha Shui ( this hotel is in Tsim sha Tsui East)or for better value in Jordan or Monkok. Did not choose to eat in the hotel at all as the prices were very high compared to local restaurants although they all appeared to be attractive and well appointed. Rooms surround a central atrium which is very attractive and is viewed from open lifts and the corridors to the rooms. However this does mean that cooking smells drift up to the rooms from the main restaurant where there is some cooking at open grills taking place and also noise from the entertainment can be heard in the rooms from ,say, 7pm to around 10pm Overall, whilst this a decent hotel, a visitor can do better elsewhere although difficult to put a finger on why we were slightly disappointed. Maybe it is the price as with very poor exchange rate at present with 拢UK it cost us approx 拢150 per night. 
