<Author>Brendan_Crowley
<Content>11th and 12th floor I stayed at the Royal Garden Hotel for three nights in 2006. The first two on the 12th floor and the last on the 11th floor. I knew the hotel was posh when I saw a Ferrari and about 10 Mercedes outside. When I arrived I was given the option of upgrading to a delux room for around $40 a night. For this I would receive my breakfast free of charge, have access to the Crown lounge and to the Sky Spa on the 17th floor amounst other things like afternoon tea and a free cocktail. In saying this my standard room also included free access to the Sky Spa and to the Crown business lounge. The reception staff were very nice and quick. The delux room was lovely. I had the usual bathroom with toothbrush, and various products by Neutrogena, a plasma TV, mini bar (expensive ,as they all are) and soft bed. There was no alarm clock which was a pity as I was worried that I would sleep in. A newspaper was delivered to the room every morning and I never saw the housekeeping but it was always done when I got back. The room also had a digital safe. The pool on the rooftop was amazing and it was nice to have a view of the city from their and relax in the jacussi. There was also a gym but I didn't go near it as I'm not that kind of person. Too lazy I guess. Anyway, I ate in the Garden Court restaurant the first night; I had half a chicken and some beef along with wine and plenty of green tea. The service and presentation was very good but I only liked the food rather than loved it. However the Jasmine tea was amazing and well worth trying even if you hate tea. The view from the glass lifts as you come down from the 12th floor are great. The hotel makes you feel special with its warm staff and luxurious surroundings. I would recommend it, thoug it is pricey. When you leave the hotel there are a number of shops very close by (if your looking for designer goods, they are everywhere and every bit as expensive as Paris, London etc). Its nice to walk around the Kowloon area and just window shop and look around and I felt that it was very safe though its a good idea to always look as if you know where you are going. The Royal Garden was in a very good location to the shops and subway and was a plesent place to stay. PS I was upgraded to the Pelican suite (at least I think that was the name) on the third day. This room was pure luxury with the best bathroom I have ever seen. This must be how wealthy politicians travel. Enjoy your holiday. 
