<Content>Excellent Hotel. Loved it! I was very impressed with the Royal Garden Hotel. The hotel atrium is gorgeous and my daughter loved going up and down the glass lifts to our room. Our room as quite large by Hong Kong Standards and I was very impressed. With all our bags and then shopping, it was good not to be staying in a shoe box (which I have previously stayed in, in Hong Kong). Whilst the views from our room (of the front of the hotel) were nothing to rave about, I would definitely stay there again. The staff were always helpful. The location was handy as it was only a short walk to the MTR and down to the star ferry. I was intially confused about whether I should stay on the Hong Kong island side or Kowloon side. However I don't think it matters as the MTR and public transport in Hong Kong is so efficient. Hong Kong is one of the easiest cities to get around. I mostly ate at fantastic local restaurants (that I found in my guidebook), and ate with the locals. And the meals were sensational. These were within walking distance of the hotel. However what I did find was that if you ate western food, then you paid triple. Avoid Tony Roma's in Kowloon unless you want to pay that much for a simple burger etc. Thankfully my little girl loves chinese food. However there is a McDonalds near the hotel if you or your kids can't go without. And there are plenty of convenience stores near the hotel too. I didn't book tours through the hotel as everything is easy to get to by foot or by public transport.One thing I would not do again is pay for coach transport to the hotel from the airport and back. Whilst it was super convenient being able to jump off directly at the hotel without carting luggage, the Royal Garden was last on the list and I visited every hotel in Kowloon first before arriving a very long long time later at ours. It drove me crazy. However with a small child it was easier. If I went back again now I wouldn't choose it unless I had hours to spare.A fantastic hotel and I think it is the best in Kowloon. 
